  "Notes": [
    {
      "Text": "Security update for MozillaFirefox",
      "Title": "Topic",
      "Type": "Summary"
    },
    {
      "Text": "This update for MozillaFirefox fixes the following issues:\n\nUpdate to Firefox Extended Support Release 140.10.1 ESR.\n\n- MFSA 2026-36 (bsc#1263110)\n  * CVE-2026-7320: Information disclosure due to incorrect boundary conditions in the Audio/Video component.\n  * CVE-2026-7321: Sandbox escape due to incorrect boundary conditions in the WebRTC: Networking component.\n  * CVE-2026-7322: Memory safety bugs fixed in Firefox ESR 115.35.1, Firefox ESR 140.10.1, Thunderbird ESR 140.10.1,\n    Firefox 150.0.1 and Thunderbird 150.0.1\n  * CVE-2026-7323: Memory safety bugs fixed in Firefox ESR 140.10.1, Thunderbird ESR 140.10.1, Firefox 150.0.1 and\n    Thunderbird 150.0.1\n",
      "Title": "Details",
      "Type": "General"
    },
